<h2>Best HVAC Systems for Savannah Climate</h2>
<p>For Savannah's hot-humid climate, heat pumps are often the optimal choice, providing both efficient cooling and adequate heating for the mild winters. Look for systems with SEER ratings of 16 or higher and HSPF ratings of at least 9.0 for maximum efficiency. Variable-speed compressors are particularly beneficial in humid climates like Savannah's, as they run longer at lower speeds to better remove humidity while maintaining consistent temperatures. Two-stage or variable-speed systems also provide better dehumidification than single-stage units, which is crucial during Savannah's humid summer months when indoor humidity control is as important as temperature control.</p>

