<p>When selecting an HVAC contractor in Savannah, verify they hold a valid Georgia contractor's license and are insured and bonded. Look for contractors with extensive experience in hot-humid climates who understand the importance of proper sizing, ductwork design, and humidity control. Request multiple quotes and ensure each contractor performs a Manual J load calculation to properly size your system ‚Äì oversized systems are common in Savannah and lead to poor humidity control and higher energy bills. Choose contractors who offer comprehensive warranties on both equipment and installation, provide 24/7 emergency service during peak summer months, and have strong local references from recent customers in the Chatham County area.</p>

